race.comment: THE KAMIKAZE (6) grows a leg for hoop Fry who has three wins and a placing from just five steers and is racing very consistently of late. Drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and should be right there at the business end. KOBAYASTAR (11) has a handy record over this track and trip with a win and four placings from just six attempts. Rarely runs a bad race and can feature in the finish while fresh. ULTIMATE (10) is a consistent commodity who has hit the top-five at his past 12 outings. Top-three credentials. PRINCE AKEEM (7) is a three-time winner here who gets 2kg off with the claim. In the mix. ALL ENGLAND (1) has strung four wins together on the bounce and is racing with a lot of confidence. Keep safe.
